          	<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0],p=/^http:/.test(d.location)?'http':'https';if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src=p+'://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js';fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document, 'script', 'twitter-wjs');</script>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="services">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 text-center">
          <h1>Project Requirements</h1>
          <hr/>
            <ol style="font-size: 1.5em;" class="fa-ul">
              <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>Project must be technical in nature (we are developers, after all)</li>
              <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>Project must NOT be for-profit</li>
              <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>Project must be <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source">open-source</a></li>
              <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>Project must be completable within 4 weeks</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="call-to-action">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 text-center">
          <h1>ProjectPHL Timeline</h1>
            <hr/>
            <p>
              <ul>
                    <li>June 16 - 27: Applications open for project submissions</li>
                    <li>June 28 - July 4: Philadelphia votes for favorite project (details soon)</li>
                    <li>July 6: Winning project announced</li>
                    <li>July 7 - August 1: Project development</li>
                    <li>August 1: Showcase project at Open Access Philly</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="services">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 text-center">
          <h1>FAQ</h1>
          <hr/>
          <p class="lead">
                <h3>What kinds of projects are you looking for?</h3>
                <h4>Any technical project that you think will benefit Philadelphia.</h4>

                <h3>Any costs to this?</h3>
                <h4>Nope. We're giving you our free engineering experience to build something great.</h4>

                <h3>Do I need to be a part of an organization or company to submit a project?</h3>
                <h4>Not at all. Anyone can submit a project idea.</h4>

                <h3>What is the timeline for ProjectPHL?</h3>
                <h4>Please take a look at our timeline above.</h4>

                <h3>Will you be working on the project after August 10th?</h3>
                <h4>As of right now, we cannot guarantee maintenance or updating of the project beyond August 10th.</h4>

                <h3>Questions?</h3>
                <h4><a href="mailto:fellows@pennapps.com">fellows@pennapps.com</a></h4>
           </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="call-to-action">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 text-center">
            <h1>The Fine Print</h1>
            <hr/>
            <ol style="font-size: 1.5em;" class="fa-ul">
                <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>PennApps Fellows will have the final say on which project is chosen.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>PennApps Fellows is not responsible for maintaining or updating the project beyond the end of its summer program on August 10th, 2014.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>PennApps Fellows does not guarantee full completion of project (but we will work our best given our timeline).</li>
                <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>The project must NOT be for-profit.</li>
                <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-check-square-o"></i>The project must be <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_source">open-source</a>.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
